\par\pard\plain \tx0\fi360\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf8 Evan:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1> Evan was filled with happiness. He had a surprise present ready for his sister Liz. With the woman he was deeply in love with, Sarah, beside him and Christmas, his favorite holiday, approaching, he was elated. The anticipation of introducing Sarah to his sister Liz and her boyfriend Joe excited him. Additionally, he looked forward to sharing cherished Christmas traditions with Sarah and Liz.<!$Scr_Cs::1>}
\par\plain \f2\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf8 Sarah: }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Sarah's feelings for Evan were undeniable. However, the prospect of accompanying him to Chicago for three days, which would likely be unproductive, wasn't appealing to her. Meeting Evan's sister didn't make her nervous, but she wasn\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8217\'92t enthusiastic. Throughout the novel, Sarah's inner struggle would be evident\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 balancing her emotional connection with Evan and the life she had always known, defined by academic achievement and work. Evan's humming along to Christmas music on the radio made it challenging for Sarah to focus.<!$Scr_Cs::1>}
\par\plain \f2\fs22\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \tx0\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf6 <$Scr_Ps::2>POV:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 <$Scr_Cs::1> Third-person limited, deep (focusing on Sarah). The focus of this scene is what's going on inside Sarah's mind. She loved Evan very much. She adored his enthusiasm for Christmas, his sister, and this trip. At the same time, it's not her cup of tea. In what she feels was becoming an undesirable pattern, she only went along to fulfill her role as Evan's girlfriend.<!$Scr_Cs::1><!$Scr_Ps::2>}
