\par\pard\plain \tx235\tx720\li576\fi-216\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch \ls4\ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 A contrast of energies existed in the 2+ hour drive from their college town to the northern suburbs of Chicago. Evan had a radio station playing Christmas tunes turned up loud, and he animatedly hummed along to the tune. He was as happy as could be.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Sarah, on the other hand, had her head buried in her laptop, working on dozens of tasks she needed to get done for upcoming holiday parties and a large fundraising event for New Year's Eve.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Evan was really excited about the Christmas present that he was going to give Liz. The specific gift wasn't revealed to the reader in this scene, but it was mentioned to create a bit of mystery about `what the present might be.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Sarah did her best to tune out the music and Evan's humming, but it drove her a little crazy. However, she didn't want to kill Evan's mood, so she looked up every now and then and smiled as he talked about the great Christmas traditions that he and Liz practiced. While Evan was looking forward to introducing Sarah to her sister and their traditions, not to mention Liz's boyfriend Joe, Sarah was trying to plot ways of sneaking in some work during the three-day trip.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 The cold gray day, to some extent, matched Sarah's mood. But she was conscious not to expose that to Evan.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Evan sensed that something was wrong with Sarah. He inquired a couple of times, but she just said she was busy with work. He wasn't completely convinced she was being forthcoming with what was on her mind, but his mood was too good to be distracted. However, he did remind her that she promised once they get to Liz's house the work would stop except for emergencies.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 There wasn't a lot of dialogue in the short scene. Here are some things that you may want to include: <!$Scr_Ps::6>}
\par\pard\plain \tx235\tx720\li994\fi-259\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch \ls5\ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i0 \uc0\u9702 	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Evan's excitement over how much Liz was going to like the present he got her.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i0 \uc0\u9702 	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Evan's excitement about the movie they watched every Christmas, but he wanted to keep it a surprise, so he didn't tell Sarah. While Evan was excited about this, Sarah's fake smile hid her desire to do anything else but watch a Christmas movie during the trip.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i0 \uc0\u9702 	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Use dialogue to show the reader that while Evan is happy, he is concerned about Sarah not keeping her promise to let work goal during the 3 days they will be at Liz's. He reminds her sternly but respectfully. She doesn't answer verbally he nods agreement.}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 <!$Scr_Cs::1>}
